edu.clarke.team2988.commands

Class FireCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • Command
      • edu.clarke.team2988.commands.CommandBase
        • edu.clarke.team2988.commands.FireCommand

  • public class FireCommand
extends CommandBase
    This class is responsible for handling joystick trigger event to shoot the Frisbee by activating the ram which is controlled by the ShooterSubsystem.

    This command is instantiated within the OI (Operator Interface) class at startup and never terminates.

    Author:
    Micheal Dowling
    See Also:
    Subsystem, CommandBase, OI

        public FireCommand()
        Constructor for FireCommand. Specifies a requirement for the Compressor subsystem. compressorSubsystem is created in CommandBase. requires() is necessary to prevent potential conflicts caused by more than one command attempting to use the same subsystem at the same time.
